  array (
    'es_ES' => '<p>Se solicita a los árbitros tener en cuenta los siguientes aspectos:</p><p>1. Pertinencia de los aportes conceptuales</p><p>2. Correcta elaboración del resumen y pertinencia del título del articulo con respecto a su contenido</p><p>3. Pertinencia y vigencia de las fuentes consultadas por el autor</p><p>4. Coherencia de los resultados con respecto a los objetivos planteados</p><p>5. Claridad metodológica</p><p>6. Estructura y redacción adecuada del artículo</p><p>7. Relevancia de los resultados con respecto al campo de conocimiento</p><p>8. Solidez en el sustento de las ideas planteadas</p><p>9. Utilidad del artículo para el ejercicio profesional y la investigación formativa</p><p>10. Ética de la investigación y de la presentación de sus resultados</p><p> </p>',
    'en_US' => '<div> </div><p style="display: inline !important;">The articles submitted for publication in the magazine must be original and unpublished, i.e., they must not have been published in print or digital media. Neither should they be in the process of being reviewed nor have any publishing commitments with another publication.</p><p>The author(s) accept(s) that reception of a document by the magazine does not imply a commitment to publish it.</p><p>The authors should submit their documents exclusively through the OJS platform using the link named “envíos en línea” (on-line submissions), on the dates of the invitations published by the magazine on the same website <a href="/index.php/sociojuridicos/index">http://revistas.urosario.edu.co/index.php/sociojuridicos/index</a> or through social networks such as Facebook or Twitter</p><p>To submit articles to the magazine, take into account the “guidelines for authors”, which contain the specifications on document presentation required by the magazine (see the preliminary list on preparation of files).</p><p>The author must certify that the article was written by him/her by filling out and signing the form “authorization for publication”. In the case of several authors, each co-author must fill out the form and submit it to the magazine with the article. If any graphics or statistical materials are used that are not of the property of the authors, the authors shall be responsible for obtaining the permits for use of said information from the competent authorities.</p><p>The submitted documents must fit into one of the following categories:</p><p><strong>Scientific or technical research article:</strong> A document that presents, in a detailed manner, the original results of research projects. The most commonly used structure has four major parts: introduction, methodology, results and conclusions.</p><p><strong>Reflection article:</strong> A document that presents research results from an analytical, interpretative or critical perspective, on a specific subject, making use of original sources.</p><p><strong>Review article:</strong> A document resulting from research that analyzes, systematizes and incorporates the results of published or non-published research in a scientific or technological field, to account for the progress made and development trends. It features a careful bibliographic review of at least fifty (50) references.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Preliminary list for preparation of submissions</strong></p><p>As part of the submission process, the authors are required to ensure that their submission fulfills all the items listed below. Any submissions that do not fulfill these requirements will be returned to the author.</p><p>When submitting the article, include the following documents:</p><p><strong>1. Cover page:</strong> The cover page should include the title of the article in Spanish and English, the name of the author(s), institutional affiliation including country and city, financing sources of the research and a brief profile of the author(s) in a maximum of four (4) lines, including the institutional e-mail address. Additionally, indicate whether the article has been presented at any congress or if it has been written for a dissertation.</p><p><strong>2. Abstract and keywords:</strong> the author(s) should include an abstract of the article with a maximum of one-hundred-twenty (120) words in Spanish and English. The abstract should be succinct and should very briefly present the objective, methodology, results and conclusions so as to enable the reader to have a full idea of the document on first reading. Also, keywords should be included to facilitate indexation of the article (a maximum of five), both in English and Spanish.</p><p><strong>3. Authorization for publication:</strong> The authors should fill out the authorization included at the end of this document, sign it and submit it physically or electronically. This is a mandatory requirement for the submission of articles to the consideration of the magazine.</p><p>General instructions on the presentation of articles:</p><ul><li>Length: Maximum 30 pages (8000 to 10000 words including bibliographical references)</li><li>Margins: 3 cm on each side of the page.</li><li>Interline Spacing: double space, including textual quotes. Do not insert tabs or extra spaces between paragraphs. Do not insert page breaks.</li><li>Font: Times New Roman, 12 points</li><li>Page numbering: lower right corner of the page</li><li>Title: In Spanish and English. If the document is written in a different language, one of the three options should be considered.</li><li>Authors: The full name of the author or authors of the document should appear under the title.</li><li>Author profile: Brief profile of the author (maximum 4 lines) including institutional affiliation, current position and institutional and personal e-mail address. This information should be included as a footnote.</li><li>Footnotes: They are used for clarification purposes and not to present the bibliography, except as a complementary reference.</li><li>Abstract: You must include a brief summary of the central idea of the text and the research performed (120 words, both in Spanish and English).</li><li>List of references: They should be placed at the end of the article using the APA 6th Edition standard.</li><li>Hierarchy of sub-titles: They must be sequential with a maximum of three levels, as follows:</li></ul><p>1. Title 1</p><p>1.1. Second level sub-title</p><p>1.1.1. Third level sub-title</p><p>2. Title 2</p><p><em>*Information taken from: Patiño Díaz, G. (2013) Escritura y Universidad. Bogotá, Colombia. Editorial Universidad del Rosario; Centro de Enseñanza y Aprendizaje.</em></p><p>If any figures or tables are included, we recommend a maximum of two colors per figure. The author is responsible for obtaining the permits and rights to include materials or illustrations.</p><p>The text must comply with bibliographical and style requirements. The references in the text and the sources must be presented according to the citation standards of the <strong>American Psychological Association (APA)</strong> 6th Edition, numbered and ordered alphabetically. All references must be cited in the text. The authors are responsible for verifying the references.</p><p>The submitted file should be in the Microsoft Word, RTF, OpenOffice or WordPerfect format and should follow the instructions to ensure a blind review.</p>',
