      array (
        'order' => '1',
        'content' => '<p>As part of the submission process, the authors are required to ensure that their submission fulfills all the items listed below. Any submissions that do not fulfill these requirements will be returned to the author.</p><p>When submitting the article, include the following documents:</p><p><strong>1. Cover page:</strong> The cover page should include the title of the article in Spanish and English, the name of the author(s), institutional affiliation including country and city, financing sources of the research and a brief profile of the author(s) in a maximum of four (4) lines, including the ORCID code of the Researcher and the institutional e-mail address. Additionally, indicate whether the article has been presented at any congress or if it has been written for a dissertation.</p><p><strong>2. Abstract and keywords:</strong> the author(s) should include an abstract of the article with a maximum of one-hundred-twenty (120) words in Spanish and English. The abstract should be succinct and should very briefly present the objective, methodology, results and conclusions so as to enable the reader to have a full idea of the document on first reading. Also, keywords should be included to facilitate indexation of the article (a maximum of five), both in English and Spanish.</p><p><strong>3. Authorization for publication:</strong> The authors should fill out the authorization included at the end of this document, sign it and submit it physically or electronically. This is a mandatory requirement for the submission of articles to the consideration of the magazine.</p><p> </p>',
