      1 => 
      array (
        'order' => '2',
        'content' => '<p>General instructions on the presentation of articles:</p><ul><li>Length: Maximum 30 pages (8000 to 10000 words including bibliographical references)</li><li>Margins: 3 cm on each side of the page.</li><li>Interline Spacing: double space, including textual quotes. Do not insert tabs or extra spaces between paragraphs. Do not insert page breaks.</li><li>Font: Times New Roman, 12 points</li><li>Page numbering: lower right corner of the page</li><li>Title: In Spanish and English. If the document is written in a different language, one of the three options should be considered.</li><li>Authors: The full name of the author or authors of the document should appear under the title.</li><li>Author profile: Brief profile of the author (maximum 4 lines) including institutional affiliation, current position and institutional, ORCID code and personal e-mail address. This information should be included as a footnote.</li><li>Footnotes: They are used for clarification purposes and not to present the bibliography, except as a complementary reference.</li><li>Abstract: You must include a brief summary of the central idea of the text and the research performed (120 words, both in Spanish and English).</li><li>List of references: They should be placed at the end of the article using the <strong>APA 6th</strong> Edition standard.</li><li>Hierarchy of sub-titles: They must be sequential with a maximum of three levels, as follows:</li></ul><p>1. Title 1</p><p>1.1. Second level sub-title</p><p>1.1.1. Third level sub-title</p><p>2. Title 2</p><p><em>*Information taken from: Patiño Díaz, G. (2013) Escritura y Universidad. Bogotá, Colombia. Editorial Universidad del Rosario; Centro de Enseñanza y Aprendizaje.</em></p><p>If any figures or tables are included, we recommend a maximum of two colors per figure. The author is responsible for obtaining the permits and rights to include materials or illustrations.</p>',
